description.en: The Wind Farm Ontology (wfont) describes wind farms and their components. It is inspired by the SANDIA Report SAND2009-1171 and DAEKIN project outcomes. It reuses the AffectedBy and EEP (Execution-Executor-Procedure) ontology design patterns to discover sensors or actuators that observe or act on a given quality or feature of interest.

comment.undefined: An agent that produces an event (Execution) by implementing a procedure.
An event made by an agent executing a task implemented by a procedure.

A quality of a feature of interest. An aspect of a feature of interest that is intrinsec to and cannot exist without the feature of interest. Every quality belongs to the feature of interest it is intrinsic to.

A feature of interest is an abstraction of a real world phenomena (object, event, etc). A feature of interest is then described in terms of its properties or qualities, which are qualifiable, quantifiable, observable or operable qualities of the feature of interest.
A workflow, protocol, plan, algorithm, or computational method specifying how to produce an event.
Relation that links an agent (Executor) to a procedure that it implements.
A relation between features of interest and qualities.
A relation between qualities. A quality is affected by another quality if the value of the latter affects the value of the former.
A relation that links an execution to the procedure used in making the execution through an executor agent.
A relation between qualities and features of interest. Every quality belongs to the feature of interest it is intrinsic to.
Relation that links an executor to the qualities acted upon by the executions it made.
Relation that links an execution to the quality it is acting upon.
Relation that links an execution to the quality it is acting upon.
A relation that links an execution to the procedure used in making the execution through an executor agent.
Relation that links an executor to the qualities acted upon by the executions it made.
A relation between qualities and features of interest. Every quality belongs to the feature of interest it is intrinsic to.
Relation that links an execution to the executor that made the execution.
Relation that links an execution to the feature of interest it is acting upon.
Relation that links an executor to the features of interest of the executions it made.
Relation that links an execution to the executor that made the execution.
